      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SIR SILVERTREE (4) flew the lids with a sensational early split last time, hitting the frame with a 0.8 lengths second (21.80) over 390m at this track and making it two placings on end. Comes through a solid form race last start. Can go on with it. COME AND SEE (2) has some solid form under her belt and proved too strong last time to win by 0.9 lengths at Geelong in a handy 22.44 beating Paw Kramer. Winner at her latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Expected to feature again. RUCKMAN (8) was in the placings last time but shapes well for this on his dynamic win the start prior, getting around Shepparton over 390m in 22.03. Has the ability and looks a key chance. PAPA EASY (7) did a good job to finish second last time out over 300m at Healesville (16.51) in a Special conditions race, the second top-three finish on the trot.",
